* ioctl in struct device_driver. This enables us to do ioctl on all devices without having functionpointer in
	class-specific fops.
	Implementation:
	
	static int driver_ioctrl(struct device* dev, int request, ..) {
		dev->driver->ioctrl(dev,request, ..);
	}
	
	#define ioctrl(devfops,request,var1,var2,var3,var4,..) driver_ioctrl(devfops,request,var1,var2,...);
	
	
* Integration of memory-management layer
* Methode to monopolize the time in a same manner.
* precision of sleeps
* meassuring of  interrupt-latencies runtime
* set timequantum at contex-shidt
* busywait fx. at small delays
* Counter on fragment-store to allow for O(1) size determination
* Design
